&lt;p&gt;The Oxford University Hospitals Bone Marrow Transplant Service was one of 10 UK centres given IMPACT status in 2017. IMPACT is a research network that enables Bone Marrow Transplant specific research to be undertaken to progress and develop treatments in this speciality. We are looking for a motivated nurse to join our established Research and Bone Marrow Transplant teams to carry out this exciting role. You will provide expert nursing care to patients referred to the Oxford Bone Marrow Transplant (BMT) service who may be eligible for enrolment into an IMPACT research trial. Experience of research nursing and clinical trials would be of benefit to candidates looking to apply however specialist knowledge and skill in Bone Marrow Transplant nursing are not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date 15/11/20&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jaimal Kothari, jaimal.kothari@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
